MLSCREENINGCONSENT:
Study Number: 2010-180

Principal Investigator: Dr. Abigail Marsh

 

Permission to Take Part in a Human Research Study

Georgetown University
Title: Mind and Wellness Study



We are conducting a study to learn more about social and psychological factors associated with wellness.



The first part of the study is an online survey. It will be a series of brief questionnaires that will ask you questions about your experiences, personality, and history, including items related to your mental health and medical history. These questions will take no longer than about 30 minutes to answer. You may also be contacted for a brief follow-up phone call to determine your eligibility for later parts of the study.



We will compensate you with $20 via Amazon eGift Card or PayPal for completing the survey. 



We will then determine if you qualify for additional parts of the study. If you are eligible, you may be invited to take part in: 

	A 4-week online meditation training
	Online questionnaires
	In-person brain scanning at Georgetown University
	In-person questionnaires at Georgetown University



We will compensate you with an additional $200 via Amazon eGift Card or PayPal for completing all parts of the study.



All parts of this study are voluntary. You don’t have to take part if you don’t want to. Even if you do qualify for the study and decide to join, you can change your mind later. Taking part in this online survey and phone call won’t benefit you directly.



We aim to protect your personal information to the extent allowed by law. Your answers to the questions in this study will not be directly linked to your identity. You will not be identified in any reports or publications resulting from this study. However, we cannot guarantee absolute confidentiality. Records of research study participants will be stored indefinitely and kept on a secure cloud storage platform to which only researchers approved on this protocol have access. In addition to the researchers and research institution(s) conducting this study, organizations that may request to inspect and/or copy your research records for quality assurance data analysis and other research related and operational or administrative purposes, include groups such as: Georgetown University, Georgetown University Institutional Review Board (IRB), federal research agencies.



Administrative personnel involved in processing your payment for participation will be aware of your identity. They will not have access to your data.



If you have questions, concerns, or complaints, talk to the research team at lsan@georgetown.edu.



This research has been reviewed and approved by an Institutional Review Board (“IRB”). You may talk to them at (202) 687-1506 or irboard@georgetown.edu if:

	Your questions, concerns, or complaints are not being answered by the research team.
	You cannot reach the research team.
	You want to talk to someone besides the research team.
	You have questions about your rights as a research subject.
	You want to get information or provide input about this research

 

If you agree to complete this online survey and phone call, please click “I consent”.
RECONTACT:
Can I participate in future research studies?
If you consent, we may also wish to contact you in the future via email or phone to invite you to participate in additional online or in-person research. If you are contacted, your participation is entirely optional. You can opt out at any time if you decide later on you would no longer like to take part. Your participation in this study will not be affected if you would prefer not to be re-contacted about participation in future studies.
